fix_guidance:
API FIX: Layer.Name is read-only. Set the name via constructor.
  - Use: var layer = new Layer("id", "My Layer Name");
  - Layer.Name and Layer.Id are set at construction time.

CRITICAL API FIX: Layer content is added via Page.Layers.
  - Access layers: page.Layers (LayerCollection on a Page).
  - Create layer: var layer = new Layer("id", "name");
  - Add content via layer.Contents (Operator list).
  - Add layer to page: page.Layers.Add(layer);
  - Do NOT use Layer.AddText() or Layer.Operators.

API FIX: CrashReportOptions.Exception is read-only.
  - Pass exception via constructor: new CrashReportOptions(ex);
  - Do NOT assign options.Exception = ex after construction.

CRITICAL API FIX: Heading class for table of contents.
  - Heading inherits from TextFragment. Set text via Segments.
  - Heading does NOT have .Title or .IsInToc properties.
  - Create: var heading = new Heading(level);
  - Set text: heading.Segments.Add(new TextSegment("text"));
  - heading.IsAutoSequence = true; for auto-numbering.
  - Add to page: page.Paragraphs.Add(heading);
